Kuwait Petroleum International
Ltd., a unit of Kuwait Petroleum Corp., will buy as much as
210,000 metric tons of ultra-low-sulfur diesel for May and June
in  Europe , according to a company official.  KPI, as the company is known, awarded a tender on April 16
which gave it the option to purchase four to seven cargoes of
the fuel amid planned maintenance at its Milazzo refinery on the
Italian island of Sicily in May, the official, who declined to
be identified citing company policy, said today in an e-mailed
response to questions. The official didnâ€™t disclose the seller
